---+!! %TOPIC%

The fragment below can be used in a sidebar navigation to establish a folder-like subweb navigation.
This uses the jqTreeview widget of the TWiki:Plugins/JQueryPlugin.

Use it by adding =%&lt;nop&gt;INCLUDE{&quot;%WEB%.%TOPIC%&quot;}%= to your WebLeftBar or TWikiWebSideBar.

If you want to hide the web navigation from &lt;nop&gt;TWikiGuests then uncomment the following:
   * #Set DENYTOPICVIEW = %MAINWEB%.TWikiGuest

&lt;verbatim&gt;
%STARTINCLUDE%&lt;!-- flexweblist tree --&gt;
%TWISTY{
  prefix=&quot;&lt;h2 &gt;&quot;
  link=&quot;Webs &quot;
  suffix=&quot;&lt;/h2&gt;&quot;
  showimg=&quot;%ICONURLPATH{&quot;plus&quot;}%&quot;
  hideimg=&quot;%ICONURLPATH{&quot;minus&quot;}%&quot;
  remember=&quot;on&quot;
}%
&lt;div class=&quot;jqTreeview closed unique&quot;&gt;
%~~ FLEXWEBLIST{
~~~   webs=&quot;%MAINWEB%,User,People,public,%TWIKIWEB%&quot; 
~~~   exclude=&quot;^(TestCases|Trash).*&quot; 
~~~   adminwebs=&quot;Applications.*&quot;
~~~   header=&quot;&lt;ul&gt;&quot;
~~~   format=&quot;&lt;li&gt;$percntWEBLINK{\&quot;$web\&quot;}$percnt&quot;
~~~   separator=&quot;&lt;/li&gt;&quot;
~~~   footer=&quot;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&quot;
~~~   subheader=&quot;&lt;ul class=\&quot;natSubWebs\&quot;&gt;&quot;
~~~ }%
&lt;/div&gt;
%ENDTWISTY%
%STOPINCLUDE%
&lt;/verbatim&gt;


